(877, "London Community Orchestra - Mary Elizabeth Brown", " <ul><li></li></ul><br><p><strong>Peter Ilych Tchaikovsky</strong><br> Violin Concerto in D, Op. 35<br>   -Mary Elizabeth Brown, violin<p><strong>Peter Ilych Tchaikovsky</strong><br> Orchestral Suite no. 1 in d, Op. 43<p>We&#39;re featuring an all-Tchaikovsky concert! Violinist, Mary-Elizabeth Brown will return to the stage playing Tchaikovsky&#39;s violin concerto in D.  You may remember Ms. Brown&#39;s incredible performance of Beethoven&#39;s violin concerto with us in 2014.  Ms. Brown is recognized on the international stage for her virtuosity and command of the violin.  She is founder and Director of Strings Around the World and music director for lake Field Music. <br><br> Tchaikovsky&#39;s Orchestral Suite no. 1 is written in 6 movements - 4 of which the orchestra will perform (movements 1, 2, 3 & 6).  The Suite was a way for Tchaikovsky to break from writing symphonies, most notably the 4th symphony written around the same time.  Although this Suite could simply be excerpts of a symphony, it has historically been seen as its own independent work.  The piece presents a wide range of styles and moods, and it was difficult for Tchaikovsky to to make it add up to coherent experience, eventually delaying its completion by one year.<br><br><strong>Single ticket prices:</strong><ul><li>Adults: $18.00<li>Seniors: $15.00<li>Students: $12.00<li>Children: 12 and under: $5.00</li></li></li></li></ul><p><br><strong>Single tickets are available:</strong><ul><li>Orchestra members<li>At the door<li>Online tickets available: <a href="http://www.onstagedirect.com/lco" rel="nofollow">www.onstagedirect.com/lco</a></li></li></li></ul><br><a href="http://www.londontourism.ca/Events/Downtown-London-Events/London-Community-Orchestra--Mary-Elizabeth-Brown#" rel="nofollow"></a></p></p></p></p>", "http://eventful.com/events/london-community-orchestra-mary-elizabeth-brown-/E0-001-097032173-1?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '24:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
