(1128, "London Community Orchestra - Christine Newland", " <ul><li></li></ul><br><p><strong>Camille Saint-Saëns</strong><br> Cello Concerto no. 1 in a, Op. 33<br>   -Christine Newland, cello<p><strong>Antonin Dvorak</strong><br> Silent Woods, B. 182<br>   -Christine Newland, cello<p><strong>César Franck</strong><br> Symphony in d<p>For over 40 years, Christine Newland held the principle cellist chair for Orchestra London, and continues to do so with WePlayOn.  Christine is a Canada Council supported artist, and has performed as solo for CBC and BBC radio & television.  Her extensive career in music has taken her all over the world, touring in Germay, Europe, Japan and Canada.  Christine will join the orchestra playing two selections - Saint-Saëns cello concerto No. 1 & Dvorak&#39;s Silent Woods. <br><br> The LCO rounds off their season in a facinating performance of César Frank&#39;s only Symphony.  The Belgian composer completed the symphony in 1888, taking two years to finalize.  The symphony was one of the last compositions in his career, performed only a year before his eventual death.<br><br><em><em>Sponsoring this concert is Brian Cunliffe, Cunliffe Hicks Wealth Management, RBC Dominion Securities</em></em><p><strong>Single ticket prices:</strong><ul><li>Adults: $18.00<li>Seniors: $15.00<li>Students: $12.00<li>Children: 12 and under: $5.00</li></li></li></li></ul><p><br><strong>Single tickets are available:</strong><ul><li>Orchestra members<li>At the door<li>Online tickets available: <a href="http://www.onstagedirect.com/lco" rel="nofollow">www.onstagedirect.com/lco</a></li></li></li></ul><br><a href="http://www.londontourism.ca/Events/Downtown-London-Events/London-Community-Orchestra--Christine-Newland#" rel="nofollow"></a></p></p></p></p></p></p>", "http://eventful.com/events/london-community-orchestra-christine-newland-/E0-001-097032169-8?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '03:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
