(1397, "FKT16FIP Fundamentals of Illustration/Painting (Grades 6 – 8) with Mike Goodge", " Wednesdays, 10 weeks/20hrs Afterschool and Youth Program is designed to help spark creativity and let kids express their own ideas and develop imagination through fun and engaging age-appropriate projects and exercises.  Programs that involve Drawing, Painting, Colour, and Illustration, will introduced specific fundamentals and techniques such as the use of line, tone, colour, and texture in achieving a sense of shape, form, depth and movement. Kids will be introduced to basics of concept, composition, perspective, focal point, contrast, and some other elements of visual communication. They will also learn how to mix colour and how to avoid creating a muddy mess on the palette.  Through fun and interesting exercises students will be challenged at their own level, to sharpen their observation and challenge their perception of the visual world.  The program fosters a nurturing yet structured approach and atmosphere, with plenty of personal attention and gentle encouragement.  Non toxic student quality water based media such as acrylic or tempera will be used in the hands-on studio-based approach. ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fkt16fip-fundamentals-ill-/E0-001-096099044-4@2016111016?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '02:30:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
