(1399, "FA16PAR Plein Air at Rosetta McLain Gardens (B/I/A) with Byron Hodgins", " Monday 9:30am-12:30pm, for 6 weeks /18 hrs  The Mighty 8 x 10 Plein Aire Landscape Painting Plein Air painting is an exciting method of painting outdoors directly from your subject to express the fleeting effects of light, structure, colour. The small, but mighty 8 by 10 sketch has a tremendous ability to hold vitality because of it&#39;s small size which naturally highlights confident and bold painterly approaches. It is suitable for small trips and for on hikes and relaxing visits to the park. This class will introduce the 8 by 10 format and some modern working methods of the Impressionists and Group of Seven that will help you express your own experiences in nature. The outdoor sessions in this class will take place in the beautiful Rosetta Gardens. Individual support for personal aesthetics and for thematic concerns will be addressed in class and on-site while painting. The mightly 8x10 format will unleash your confidence propel your practice to journey into landscape painting. Let&#39;s get started! ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16par-plein-air-rosetta-/E0-001-096014973-0@2016111009?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '10:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
