(1432, "FA16DPVM Drawing and Painting of Various Motifs (B/I/A) Nada Sesar Raffay", " Thursdays 6:30-9:30pm 10weeks/30hrs Students will learn How to start drawing and painting and how to build an artwork; Using various material: charcoal, pen, pencil, ink, oil  chalk pastel, acrylic paint, oil paint, watercolour, collage and mixed media. Students will learn to understand various medium through experimenting variety of technique and style, from traditional to modern art approach through various thematic/motive.  ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16dpvm-drawing-and-pain-/E0-001-095983995-2@2016111018?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '04:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
INSERT INTO evenement
(noEvenement, titre, description, siteWeb, duree, imageAffiche)
VALUES
(1433, "FA16WP Watercolour Painting (B/I/A) with Marija Barac Jandric", " Tuesdays 9:30am-12:30pm for 11 weeks /33hrs Traditional Watercolour requires utmost discipline and focus in order to succeed. It does not tolerate mistakes very well, and trying to recover from them is mostly useless. However, a fast evolving modern technology has also affected the paint industry, creating new materials and changing and altering the properties of existing ones. As a result the medium of watercolour has also changed, allowing it to be much more forgiving and versatile, opening up exciting new opportunities to play and experiment with it much more freely. This course is designed for those ready to “let watercolour loose”, painting outdoors in the Bluffs when weather allows and from own sketches and notes when in the studio. Learn hands-on how to turn “mistakes” into desirable effects, while taking the journey into the unknown watercolour territory. It is recommended that you carry and use a sketchbook and a HB pencil at all times. We will look at important watercolour work of traditional as well as work by some contemporary artists. Plenty of personal attention and one to one feedback available. Materials list will be provided. ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16wp-watercolour-painti-/E0-001-095984014-3@2016111009?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '06:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
INSERT INTO evenement
(noEvenement, titre, description, siteWeb, duree, imageAffiche)
VALUES
(1434, "FA16PPH Painting from Photographs (B/I) with Marija Barac Jandric", " Wenesdays 9:30am-12:30pm for 10 weeks/27 hrs As you probably know from experience, it is not simple to paint from a photograph, as the result is often a disappointing flatness and dullness. This course teaches what it takes to translate a photo image into a painting composition. You will learn hands-on how to “read” the photo, and how to select and correctly interpret the visual information captured by the camera. You can work in a medium of your choosing, while it is strongly recommended to carry and use a sketchbook and a HB pencil at all times. Previous drawing and painting experience is a plus, but it’s not a requirement for this course. Materials list will be provided.  ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16pph-painting-photogra-/E0-001-096078245-6@2016111009?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '48:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
