(1437, "FA16DE Drawing Exploration (B/I/A) with Ashley Johnson", " Tuesdays 1:00-4:00pm for 10 weeks/30hrs Drawing is so fundamental to human experience that we don&#39;t even think about it much. Kids draw before they learn to speak, and drawing is the first form of creative expression for a child. As we grow up we often forget how much fun drawing can be. This course will shed light on some traditional approaches to formal drawing, but it will mainly show and inspire a more contemporary expression based on the use of line. We will discuss how some drawing materials evolved and changed, while other ones remain the same for centuries and even millenia. A topic of digital drawing will also be addressed in the context of contemporary drawing tools. Be prepared for exploration and discovery on this journey. A lots of personal attention, hands-on-demonstrations, and class critiquing are  essential parts of the course. Materials list will be provided. ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16de-drawing-exploratio-/E0-001-095983891-7@2016111013?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '02:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
