(1439, "FA16IML Impressionist Landscape (B/I/A) with Olga Battaglia", " Tuesday 1:00-4:00pm 11weeks/33hrs Colour owes it’s existence, and it’s appearance to light. Impressionist technique has resulted from the approach of trying to capture the observed impressions of colour affected by light, rather than the “real colour”. Paintings produced this way are dynamic, full of movement, and exceptionally beautiful. In this course students will work mainly from their own photographs depicting a scene with a strong sense of light and shadow. Emphasis will be on achieving a convincing sense of form, volume and spatial depth using a “colour priority” method of impressionist painting. Students will be coached on colour mixing in order to gain better command of tertiary colours, trying to avoid flatness and pastiness in their work. The objective is to produce at least two paintings per term, in either acrylic or oil or both, depending on what a student will choose to work with. This course is best suited for students with some previous painting experience. Material list provided.  ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16iml-impressionist-lan-/E0-001-095983864-3@2016111013?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '01:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
