(1441, "FA16LDPS Life Drawing and Painting Studio (B/I/A) with Marija Barac Jandric", " Tuesday 1:00-4:00pm 9weeks /27hrs, model fee included This course provides an opportunity for a sustained study of a pose over a period of several weeks. You will be encouraged to develop a personal approach and style through an informed, guided, and structured process of painting based on observation and keen perception. It is recommended to use water based medium such as acrylic, due to it’s fast drying time and easy care and handling. We will look at and discuss various samples of contemporary figure/portrait art, as well as some examples from art history. The goal is to successfully achieve illusion of form, depth, volume, weight, and space, through scale, proportion, tonal value, perspective, and use of colour. Model fee applies and materials list will be provided.  ", "http://toronto.eventful.com/events/fa16ldps-life-drawing-and-/E0-001-095983852-8@2016111013?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '10:00:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
