(2219, "Tim Gray", " <br> Tim Gray has been performing comedy in Winnipeg since 2007. He holds a bachelors degree in Dramatic Arts from the University of Manitoba. It was at that school that Tim founded the U of M Comedy Club, started producing shows for his improv group, and started a weekly sketch show on UMFM with Dan Huen called The Gray Area of Comedy. In 2011 he co-wrote and co-directed a sketch show for the Winnipeg Fringe called Full Screen Ahead with Stephen Sim (CRUMBS). Uptown Magazine gave the show 4.5/5 stars. In the same year, the television show The Week Thus Far launched on ShawTV. He currently holds five titles on that weekly satirical news/talk show including Writer and Segment Coordinator. Tim has been passionately pursuing stand-up comedy for over three years now and could not be more excited to be a part of the Winnipeg Comedy Festival.", "http://eventful.com/winnipeg/events/tim-gray-/E0-001-096985742-5?utm_source=apis&utm_medium=apim&utm_campaign=apic", "INTERVAL '02:30:00' HOUR TO MINUTE", NULL);
