Join us for this 7-week course to learn how to use the power of a focused mind to analyze habitual ingrained patterns of thought, philosophical points, and other aspects of the path. Analytical meditation is critical for enhancing the benefits of calm abiding meditation and vice versa. The two forms of meditation are complementary. Calm Abiding cultivates the ability to focus single-pointedly and Analytical meditation uses this clarity of mind to examine various states of mind and points of philosophy. Once the mind has gained certainty on the points being examined then the meditator switches back to Calm Abiding and rests the mind in that certainty. Through this alternation of the two practices one&#39;s meditation continually deepens.

